Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a #full kettle{}.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, sprinkle over half the @Cajun spice mix{1/2%sachet} and toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Place the @slow cooked British pork{425%grams} and its juices into an #ovenproof dish{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining @Cajun spice mix{1/2%sachet}, cover with #foil{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven until piping hot and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is piping hot throughout.

While everything roasts, drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{}. Halve the @lime{1/2}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Once charred, remove the pan from the heat.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{64%grams} with a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper. Mix well.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lime juice if needed.

Add the charred corn and @coleslaw mix{120%grams} to the bowl and toss to coat. Set aside.

When 5 mins of roasting time remain, pop the @burger buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the pork from the oven, then discard the foil and any cooking juices. Use two #forks{} to gently break apart the pork.

Mix through the @BBQ sauce{64%grams} and @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp}.

> See pantry for ketchup amount.

When everything's ready, fill your burger buns with the BBQ pulled pork and some of the charred corn slaw.

Serve with your wedges and any remaining slaw alongside.

Enjoy!